item.description:
arXiv:2412.07875v1 Announce Type: new 
Abstract: In this paper we consider the following Sturm-Liouville equation \[ \left\{ \begin{aligned}
  -(x^{2\alpha}u'(x))'+u(x)&=f(x) && \text{in } (0,1],\\ u(1)&=0 \end{aligned} \right. \] where $\alpha<1$ is a nonzero real number and $f$ belongs to $L^p(0,1)$ for $p\geq 1$. We analyze the existence and regularity of solutions under suitable weighted Dirichlet boundary condition at the origin.
